currently in development

uses Pimoroni Keybow to control SmartSDR via CAT interface
https://shop.pimoroni.com/products/keybow-mini-3-key-macro-pad-kit?variant=27890390696019
https://roskosch.de/smartsdr-for-mac/


Left key shifts current frequency down with a configurable frequency shift
Middle key is PTT toggle ... release has a configurable delay between 100ms en 500ms
Right key shifts current frequency up with a configurable frequency shift

## Getting started

### Running web interface with docker-compose

- Install docker compose https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/
- Run ``docker-compose up``
- The interface is running on localhost:80

### Running on Raspberry Pi
- Install nodejs and yarn on the raspberry
- Make sure that the enviorment variables ``REDIS_HOST`` and ``REDIS_PORT`` are set
- Go to the web folder of this project
- Run ``yarn`` to download all dependencies 
- Run ``yarn build`` to compile the application
- Run ``sudo yarn start`` to start the application. We need to run this as a privilaged user to bind to port 80 
- The application is now running on localhost:80